{
  "text": "To measure the effects of the tested ligands on osteoblast mineralization, U-33/γ2 U-33/c cells were initially cultured for 6 days with or without ligands, as described above, followed by 13 days culture in pro-osteoblastic medium containing 0.2 mM ascorbic acid (Sigma) and 10 mM β-glycerophosphate (Sigma) [CITATION_1] . The culture medium was replaced every other day. Calcium deposited into the extracellular matrix was extracted with 0.1% acetic acid for 5 h at room temperature, and quantified colorimetrically using a Calcium Binding Assay (Sigma).",
